---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/docs.astro'
---

<DocsLayout page="/">
  <h1>Introduction</h1>
  <p>
    <code>func</code> is a modern command line framework that is lighter and more elegant
    than comparable tools, while still offering scaffolding support and an excellent developer
    experience.
  </p>
  <p>
    <code>func</code> is built with <code>TypeScript</code>, making it easier to
    maintain and extend. Type support gives you rich syntax hints, but the workflow
    stays simple: one command is enough from development to packaging.
  </p>
  <p>
    You can create a project in seconds with the <a href="/guide"
      >Quick-start Guide</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h2>Features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Very small bundle size, approximately <a
        href="https://github.com/unix/func/blob/master/examples/gzbundle/archived.tar.gz"
        >7 KB</a
      >
    </li>
    <li>Elegant syntax without extra mental overhead</li>
    <li>
      Very few dependencies, optimizing runtime speed and <code>npm</code> download time
    </li>
    <li>Project template support</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why</h2>
  <p>
    For <code>func</code>, using decorator metadata to define commands is a
    lightweight choice. Most of that code is not carried into runtime after the
    build, while the development experience still benefits from hints, types, and
    clear structure.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you need to rebuild a tool or start a new one from the beginning,
    <code>func</code> is a good choice for building command-line tools in a simple and
    enjoyable way.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
